Much of the progress in the field is owed to the rapidly increasing capabilities of computers. At the end of the DARPA program in 1976, the best computer available to researchers was the  WIKILINK  with 4 MB ram.<ref name=\"Communications of the ACM\"/> It could take up to 100 minutes to decode just 30 seconds of speech. REFERENCE

Two practical products were:
* '''1987''' – a recognizer from Kurzweil Applied Intelligence
* '''1990''' – Dragon Dictate, a consumer product released in 1990 REFERENCE <ref name=\"KurzweilAIbio\">{{cite web |url=http://www.kurzweilai.net/ray-kurzweil-bio |title=Ray Kurzweil biography |publisher=KurzweilAINetwork |date= |accessdate=25 September 2014
